From 30d9847493a8f105b76be172a9b8e76b88fca545 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: David Allsopp <david.allsopp@metastack.com>
Date: Sat, 8 Feb 2025 10:13:18 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix the detection of Cygwin-like build environments

Both Cygwin and MSYS2 are now consistently detected on MSYS2. In
particular, this means that ./configure --prefix $PWD/install and
similar will cause the prefix to be correctly translated to a Windows
path, as already happens on Cygwin.

(cherry picked from commit 2c9b00528eb82f56b45c29525271c81ee0b0c16b)

diff --git a/Changes b/Changes
index 333b89535487d37dd26e940e142b2f890ff9ef63..216168d0db3cf41bb6284d5d2a631c99cb390c65 100644
--- a/Changes
+++ b/Changes
@@ -72,6 +72,12 @@ OCaml 4.14 maintenance version
   --disable-shared.
   (David Allsopp, review by ???)
 
+- #14???: Normalise `--prefix` when compiling on MSYS2 in the same way as is
+  already done on Cygwin. In particular, backslashes are converted to slashes
+  and MSYS2-style paths (e.g. resulting from `--prefix $PWD/install`) are
+  converted to Windows-style paths.
+  (David Allsopp, review by ???)
+
 ### Bug fixes:
 
 - #12070, #12075, #13209: auto-detect whether `ar` support @FILE arguments at
